<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="129" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="129">
This species has the following characteristics: the apical and medial lobes of the outer lobes are separated in the lower lip; the carpus of male gnathopod 1 is about 1.8 times as long as the propodus; the palm of the male gnathopod 2 has a sloped quadrate hump and posterodistal tooth. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bulycheva, AI" journalOrPublisher="Trudy Zoologicheskogo Instituta" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="195 - 250" refId="B5" refString="Bulycheva, AI, 1952. Novue vidy bokoplavov (Amphipoda, Gammaridea) iz Japonskogo Morja. Akademiia Nauk SSSR. Trudy Zoologicheskogo Instituta 12: 195 - 250" title="Novue vidy bokoplavov (Amphipoda, Gammaridea) iz Japonskogo Morja. Akademiia Nauk SSSR." volume="12" year="1952">Bulycheva (1952)</bibRefCitation>
noted that 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. tarasovi" order="Amphipoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tarasovi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">A. tarasovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very abundant in macroalgae and reefs in Petra Velikogo Bay and in the northern Sea of Japan.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
